        "This is a paradoxical question because technology simultaneously simplifies and complicates. In many transactional aspects of life — banking, communication, information retrieval — technology has dramatically reduced friction and saved time. However, this simplification has introduced new layers of complexity. The constant connectivity creates an expectation of immediate responsiveness. The sheer volume of information available creates decision fatigue and anxiety about missing crucial updates. Moreover, the systems we rely on are themselves increasingly complex and opaque, leaving users vulnerable to surveillance, manipulation, and technical failure. The net effect is not easily characterised as purely simplifying or complicating.",
